irotoris/kube-sqs-autoscaler.body:
@irotoris Thanks for maintaining `kube-sqs-autoscaler`!

This PR seeks to make the list of queue attribute names to query in calculating the number of messages configurable via a `-attribute-names` CLI flag. The change is backwards compatible, as the queried attribute names continue to default to the following values if no `-attribute-names` flag is passed:

```golang
[]*string{
  aws.String("ApproximateNumberOfMessages"),
  aws.String("ApproximateNumberOfMessagesDelayed"),
  aws.String("ApproximateNumberOfMessagesNotVisible"),
}
```

This change is valuable to those users who'd like to use `kube-sqs-autoscaler`, but who would benefit from more granular control of how the queue message count is calculated in driving their autoscaling.
